race.comment: The Victorian visitor WHISKEY JOE (1) looked good leading all the way to win on debut at Sale and, if he makes the trip across the border, he can measure up here and prove hard to beat. Expecting some natural improvement and he might be able to roll forward and take some catching. SIR MYKA (3) might be the best of the locals. He's won two from five and drops back in grade after running well in a stronger Stakes race at Flemington during Cup week. He is versatile and can roll forward as well. DAMELLI (7) ran on powerfully from last to win a city-class maiden last start. This is harder but she's progressive and looks capable of progression. STAR COMPASS (4) is an each-way chance if he comes to this race, while COMMON INTEREST (5) is a work in progress but hasn't done much wrong in two starts and is worth including in wider plays.
